  <refnamediv>
    <refname>&package;</refname>
    <refpurpose>A simple yum-compatible wrapper for rpm</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>&package;</command>
      <arg><option>--verbose</option></arg>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsect1>
    <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
    <para>
      This manual page documents briefly the <command>&package;</command> command.
    </para>
    <para>
      <command>&package;</command> allows you to query the system package database
      and remote repository data.
      It also allows you to update repository data where required.
      This tool is not designed to be used by the end user.
      End users should either use PackageKit or yum directly.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
  <refsect1>
    <title>ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES</title>
    <para>Setting <command>ZIF_DEPSOLVE_DEBUG</command> is useful for
    debugging dependency depsolve failurs.
    </para>
  </refsect1>
